            "type": "devotion",
            "title": "Daily Devotional",
            "value": "%3Cp%3EWe%20call%20the%20leading%20character%20in%20a%20movie%2C%20a%20play%2C%20or%20an%20athletic%20event%20the%20star.%20God%20has%20a%20Star%20and%20desires%20that%20every%20eye%20be%20upon%20Him!%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EIn%20his%20final%20prophecies%2C%20Balaam%20saw%20a%20vision%20of%20a%20star%20rising%20out%20of%20Jacob.%20In%20the%20distance%20beyond%20the%20camp%20of%20Israel%2C%20Balaam%20could%20see%20Israel's%20supreme%20Leader%20who%20would%20crush%20Moab.%20When%20the%20devil%20looks%20out%20over%20the%20Church%2C%20he%20is%20blinded%20by%20the%20light%20of%20our%20Bright%20and%20Morning%20Star%2C%20the%20Lord%20Jesus%20Christ.%20Jesus%20rises%20above%20all%20our%20enemies%20in%20His%20glory.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EThe%20shepherds%20saw%20the%20Star%20of%20all%20history%20face-to-face%20the%20night%20He%20was%20born%20in%20a%20manger%20(Luke%202%3A16).%20Tradition%20says%20the%20star%20Balaam%20saw%20was%20the%20same%20one%20the%20wise%20men%20followed%20from%20the%20East%20to%20find%20Christ.%20Moved%20by%20the%20Spirit%2C%20Simeon%20entered%20the%20temple%20and%20held%20in%20his%20arms%20the%20%22light%20to%20reveal%20God%20to%20the%20nations%22%20(Luke%202%3A32).%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EMay%20we%20never%20move%20our%20eyes%20away%20from%20the%20Centerpiece%20of%20God's%20universe%3A%20Jesus%2C%20the%20Star%20of%20Jacob.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%0A"
        },
